{"title_page": "Pelado Hill", "text_new": "{{short description|Inactive volcano of Costa Rica}}\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Pelado Hill\n| native_name = Cerro Pelado\n| native_name_lang = es\n| photo = \n| photo_caption = \n| elevation = {{convert|680|m|ft}}\n| map = Costa Rica\n| map_caption = Costa Rica\n| label_position = right\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.368853|N|85.014233|W|type:mountain_region:CR_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref =\n| type = [[Extinct volcano]]\n| last_eruption = Unknown\n| age =\n}}\n\n'''Pelado Hill''', from Spanish {{lang|es|Cerro Pelado}}, also known as ''Pelado Peak'', is an extinct volcano located {{convert|12|km}} SE from [[Ca\u00f1as (canton)]].<ref name=\"induni\">{{cite book |last1=Alvarado Induni |first1=Guillermo |title=Los volcanes de Costa Rica |publisher=Editorial de la Universidad Estatal a Distancia |isbn=978-9968-316-79-8 |pages=200-201}}</ref><ref name=\"rsn\">{{cite web |title=Volcanes de Costa Rica - Cerro Pelado|url=https://rsn.ucr.ac.cr/rsn/doi/13-vulcanologia/volcanes-de-costa-rica/78-pelado |website=RSN UCR |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Toponymy ==\n\n{{lang|es|Pelado}} translates to bare or naked, in this case, lack of forest canopy. \n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nExtinct for millions of years and highly eroded, the skeletal structure of the volcano caldera can still be appreciated. There is secondary activity nearby with hot springs and minerals. <ref name=\"rsn\" /> \n\n== Social and economic activity == \n\nThe hill is located in a private area made of eight properties and around {{convert|200|ha|acre}}, tourism in the area boomed from 2007 onwards, as trails were built towards the peak of the hill and some rudimentary visitor facilities were built.  Social networks such as Instagram and their influencers promoted the area due to the photogenic nature of the place. <ref>{{cite news |last1=Poltroneri |first1=Marcelo |title=Cerro Pelado: el volc\u00e1n de moda en Costa Rica |url=https://www.lateja.cr/nacional/cerro-pelado-el-volcan-de-moda-en-costa-rica/BIJXK73BTRHITASHAXNAXFJVC4/story/ |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Rodr\u00edguez Valverde |first1=Andrea |title=Cerro Pelado: An Ode to its Immensity |url=https://vozdeguanacaste.com/en/cerro-pelado-an-ode-to-its-immensity/ |accessdate=13 April 2020 |agency=The Voice of Guanacaste |date=25 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of volcanoes in Costa Rica]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Volcanoes of Costa Rica}}\n{{Mountains of Costa Rica}}\n{{Central American volcanoes}}\n\n[[Category:Stratovolcanoes of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Geography of Lim\u00f3n Province]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Inactive volcano of Costa Rica}}\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Pelado Hill\n| native_name = Cerro Pelado\n| native_name_lang = es\n| photo = \n| photo_caption = \n| elevation = {{convert|680|m|ft}}\n| map = Costa Rica\n| map_caption = Costa Rica\n| label_position = right\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.368853|N|85.014233|W|type:mountain_region:CR_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref =\n| type = [[Extinct volcano]]\n| last_eruption = Unknown\n| age =\n}}\n\n'''Pelado Hill''', from Spanish {{lang|es|Cerro Pelado}}, also known as ''Pelado Peak'', is an extinct volcano located {{convert|12|km}} SE from [[Ca\u00f1as]].<ref name=\"induni\">{{cite book |last1=Alvarado Induni |first1=Guillermo |title=Los volcanes de Costa Rica |publisher=Editorial de la Universidad Estatal a Distancia |isbn=978-9968-316-79-8 |pages=200-201}}</ref><ref name=\"rsn\">{{cite web |title=Volcanes de Costa Rica - Cerro Pelado|url=https://rsn.ucr.ac.cr/rsn/doi/13-vulcanologia/volcanes-de-costa-rica/78-pelado |website=RSN UCR |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Toponymy ==\n\n{{lang|es|Pelado}} translates to bare or naked, in this case, lack of forest canopy. \n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nExtinct for millions of years and highly eroded, the skeletal structure of the volcano caldera can still be appreciated. There is secondary activity nearby with hot springs and minerals. <ref name=\"rsn\" /> \n\n== Social and economic activity == \n\nThe hill is located in a private area made of eight properties and around {{convert|200|ha|acre}}, tourism in the area boomed from 2007 onwards, as trails were built towards the peak of the hill and some rudimentary visitor facilities were built.  Social networks such as Instagram and their influencers promoted the area due to the photogenic nature of the place. <ref>{{cite news |last1=Poltroneri |first1=Marcelo |title=Cerro Pelado: el volc\u00e1n de moda en Costa Rica |url=https://www.lateja.cr/nacional/cerro-pelado-el-volcan-de-moda-en-costa-rica/BIJXK73BTRHITASHAXNAXFJVC4/story/ |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Rodr\u00edguez Valverde |first1=Andrea |title=Cerro Pelado: An Ode to its Immensity |url=https://vozdeguanacaste.com/en/cerro-pelado-an-ode-to-its-immensity/ |accessdate=13 April 2020 |agency=The Voice of Guanacaste |date=25 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of volcanoes in Costa Rica]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Volcanoes of Costa Rica}}\n{{Mountains of Costa Rica}}\n{{Central American volcanoes}}\n\n[[Category:Stratovolcanoes of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Geography of Lim\u00f3n Province]]\n", "name_user": "Roqz", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pelado_Hill"}
